observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

Require strict compliance by the Bids and Awards Committee with the provisions of RA 9184 in the conduct of public bidding and awarding of the contracts/projects. BAC member, BAC secretariat and the TWG should familiarize themselves with different rules and regulations set forth by the said RA;

Attached excerpt copy of PPMP and APP of the projects contracted;

Adhere to the transparency provision as this is one of the governing principles on government procurement. BAC should invite in writing a representative from COA, NGO and private organization as observers as provided in the Section 13 of RA 9184 in all stages of the procurement process;

Strictly adhere to post all government procurement opportunities, results of bidding and related information in the PhilGEPS website;

Ensure that bidders submit complete eligibility requirements and all documentary requirements prior to the signing of the contract; and

Submit written justifications as to why violations to some provisions of RA 9184 were committed.

