Submit written justifications as to why violations to some provisions of RA 9184 were committed.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive:
1. Require the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) with coordination of the Municipal Engineer to submit at the beginning of the year  to the Auditor a list of all on-going government projects /programs/ activities (“PPA”) and those that are to be implemented during the year as provided for in                    Section 2.1 of COA Circular No. 2013-004 dated January 30, 2014. Likewise, maintain and submit a Monthly Monitoring Report on the Project Status every 3rd day of the following month;

2. Direct the BAC to require the winning bidder to post performance security within the period as stipulated in the Notice of Award and prior to the signing of the contract in adherence to Section 39.1 of the Revised IRR of RA 9184;

3. Head of the Procuring Entity (HOPE) award the contract only if the winning bidder post a performance security prior to the signing of the contract and forfeit the bid securities for failure to post pursuant to                Section 41 (b) of Revised IRR of RA 9184 and Section 40.1 of Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and Section 5 of GPPB issued Resolution No. 15-2014 dated 30 August 2013; and

4. HOPE enforce the Bid Securing Declaration of the winning bidder and demand in writing the payment of the fine within fifteen (15) days from receipt of the written demand as provided for in GPPB Resolution No. 15-2014 dated 30 August 2013.

